Iavan Pijoos, News24 Johannesburg - A group of high school pupils were seen looting shops in Fordsburg, Johannesburg on Wednesday afternoon.  Video footage supplied to News24 shows a large group going in and out of a shop, carrying goods.  However police spokesperson Captain Kay Makhubela denied claims that there was looting. He said a large group of students were handing over a memorandum to the department of education.  It is still unclear if the two events are connected, or what the demands of the students were.   Looting in Fordsburg. (Supplied)   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  